cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.SY

This paper is primarily focused on the analysis of neural network architectures and their ability to multitask. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper uses graph-theoretic analysis to study multitasking, which suggests that it could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper's focus on parallel processing and network design could also make it relevant to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
